  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to evaluate the clinical performance of the rotating platform
      and fixed bearing implants in patients undergoing primary total knee replacement. Outcome
      scoring and radiographic assessment will be the methods used to evaluate performance.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      This study will evaluate the clinical performance of rotating platform and fixed bearing knee
      implants. This will be done by obtaining a series of primary total knee replacements.
      Patients will receive either the P.F.C.® Sigma™ Rotating Platform Cruciate Retaining Knee
      System or the P.F.C.® Sigma™ Fixed Cruciate Retaining Knee System and assignment is
      randomized.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
