  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Knee Society Scores</measure>
    <time_frame>Pre-operative, 6 and 12 months and annually thereafter for at least 5 years.</time_frame>
    <description>The Knee Society Score (KSS) is comprised to two sections (each worth 100 points) for a maximum 200 points. One section is the Knee Society Clinical Score (KSCS) - points are given for pain, motion, and stability and points are deducted for flexion contracture, extension lag, and misalignment. The other section is the Knee Society Functional Score (KSFS) - points are assigned for walking distances and climbing stairs and points are deducted for use of walking aids. For each section, a score of 80-100 = excellent, 70-79 = good; 60-69 = fair; and &lt; 60 = poor.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
